• Tile Editor functionality is a single-page PixiJS editor with tweakpane controls. tile-editor.html defines the layout (header, controls panel, values panel, canvas, edit pane). src/tile-editor.ts wires up › Write tests for @filename 98% context left · ? for shortcutsM
  PixiJS, lets you double‑click to create a regular polygon from an expression, drag polygons, pan the view, select a polygon to edit per‑edge length and per‑vertex angle expressions, and renders hover/M
  selection/closure state with dashed/dotted strokes. vite.config.ts registers tile-editor.html as a build entry so it can be served/built alongside other pages.M
M
  Code QualityM
M
  - src/tile-editor.ts is functional and mostly readable, but it’s a large monolith handling UI, rendering, geometry, and parsing in one class; this makes it harder to test and maintain.
  - Several methods are effectively dead or incomplete (drawPolygonShape is unused, updatePreview just clears), which suggests unfinished or leftover code.
  - Type safety is loose in event handlers (e: any); there’s no cleanup of event listeners or the ResizeObserver.
  - Error handling is user‑blocking (alert in evaluate/apply), and innerHTML is used for the values display (safe here but still a pattern to watch).

  Duplicated Code

  - Angle unit parsing logic appears twice: TileEditor.parseAngleUnit and ExpressionParser.parseAngleUnit in src/tile-editor.ts.
  - drawDashedPath repeats the same segment-walking logic twice for primary/secondary colors; it’s essentially the same loop with an offset.
  - evaluateSideLengthExpression and evaluateAngleExpression are thin wrappers around evaluateExpression and could be consolidated.

  Refactoring Suggestions

  - Split src/tile-editor.ts into modules: geometry utilities (point math, polygon building), rendering (Pixi drawing), UI state (tweakpane + DOM), and expression parsing. This would reduce the class size and
    clarify responsibilities.
  - Centralize angle unit parsing (one helper shared by TileEditor and ExpressionParser) and consider moving ExpressionParser to its own file.
  - Extract a single “draw dashed line” helper used by both passes in drawDashedPath to remove duplicated segment logic.
  - Remove or finish unused methods (drawPolygonShape, updatePreview) to keep intent clear.
  - Replace any event types with Pixi’s pointer event types and add teardown for observers/listeners if you ever destroy the editor instance.

